m%2Findia%2Findias-health-ministry-challenges-measles-vaccine-data-in-2022%2Fcid%2F1980950%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20health%20ministry%20said%20UN%20data%20on%20India%20does%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20reflect%20the%20true%20picture%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20Health%20Management%20Information%20System%20shows%20that%2026%2C363%2C270%20among%2026%2C384%2C580%20eligible%20children%20had%20received%20the%20measles%20first%20dose%20during%202022-23%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20also%20said%20that%20it%20had%20taken%20multiple%20initiatives%20to%20ensure%20that%20all%20children%20receive%20all%20measles%20vaccine%20doses.%20Going%20by%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20data%2C%20India%20has%20achieved%2095%25%20coverage%20which%20is%20imperative%20to%20combat%20the%20virus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Ftb-tuberculosis-india-goals-detection%5C%22%3E%20India%20Improves%20in%20Tuberculosis%20Detection%20but%20Misses%20Major%20Death%2C%20Incidence%20Milestones%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20according%20to%20the%20experts%20quoted%20by%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Findias-health-ministry-challenges-measles-vaccine-data-in-2022%2Fcid%2F1980950%5C%22%3Egeographic%20distribution%20of%20the%20missed%20doses%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20needed%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20immunisation%20gaps%20have%20left%20children%20in%20some%20pockets%20vulnerable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20measles%2C%20we%20need%2095%25%20coverage%20at%20all%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20state%2C%20district%2C%20city%2C%20town%2C%20village%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tarun%20Bhatnagar%2C%20a%20scientist%20and%20public%20health%20specialist%20in%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Epidemiology%2C%20Chennai%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E.%20A%20cou