only%20by%20their%20son%2C%20but%20also%20by%20their%20neighbours%2C%20their%20friends%2C%20by%20their%20city%2C%20and%20perhaps%2C%20most%20painfully%2C%20by%20history%20and%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reader%20senses%20their%20isolation%20%E2%80%93%20and%20worse%20than%20isolation%2C%20their%20shame%20%E2%80%93%20which%20teaches%20them%20to%20conceal%2C%20from%20each%20other%20and%20even%20from%20themselves%2C%20their%20ardent%20yet%20unspeakable%20desire%20for%20a%20place%20where%20they%20would%20not%20feel%20irreparably%20misplaced.%20The%20intensity%20of%20this%20desire%2C%20however%2C%20is%20revealed%20only%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20story.%20Pyari%2C%20who%20had%20earlier%20given%20up%20eating%20mutton%20after%20hearing%20that%20the%20meat%20of%20ageing%20cows%20is%20often%20sold%20as%20mutton%20%E2%80%93%20who%20had%20felt%20revulsion%20and%20disgust%20at%20the%20very%20image%20of%20cow%20slaughter%20%E2%80%93%20takes%20a%20different%20position%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20story%3A%20%E2%80%9CHaving%20one%E2%80%99s%20throat%20slit%20is%20better%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20observes%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthan%20being%20abandoned%E2%80%9D.%20If%20earlier%20she%20had%20found%20her%20moorings%20in%20relating%20to%20the%20cow%20as%20a%20sacred%20and%20symbolic%20creature%20%E2%80%93%20and%20through%20the%20cow%2C%20in%20relating%20to%20the%20Hindu%20community%20%E2%80%93%20now%20she%20spontaneously%20identifies%20with%20the%20cow%20as%20an%20abandoned%20creature%2C%20one%20from%20whom%20care%20and%20fellowship%20has%20been%20withdrawn.%20Yes%2C%20death%20seems%20kinder%20than%20such%20abandonment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20319px)%2085vw%2C%20319px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19165458%2F81XOy8M17EL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22319%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19165458%2F81XOy8M17EL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20650w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19165458%2F81XOy8M17EL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-195x300.jpg%20195w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685428%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22491%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHari%20Krishna%20Kaul%2C%20translated%20from%20Kashmiri%20by%20Kalpana%20Raina%2C%20Tanveer%20Ajsi%2C%20Gowhar%20Fazili%20and%20Gowhar%20Yaqoob%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3EFor%20Now%20It%20Is%20Night%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3EHarper%20Perennial%2C%202023%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sense%20of%20having%20been%20forsaken%20merges%20quietly%20with%20the%20shame%20of%20encountering%20one%E2%80%99s%20essential%20superfluity.%20These%20short%20stories%20by%20the%20towering%20Kashmiri%20writer%2C%20Hari%20Krishna%20Kaul%20(1934-2009)%2C%20translated%20from%20Kashmiri%20by%20Kalpana%20Raina%2C%20Tanveer%20Ajsi%2C%20Gowhar%20Fazili%20and%20Gowhar%20Yaqoob%2C%20bring%20into%20view%20a%20figure%20of%20the%20Batta%2C%20the%20Kashmiri%20Pandit%2C%20that%20one%20never%20encounters%20in%20popular%20Indian%20discourse%20about%20Kashmir.%20Compulsively%20replaying%20shrill%20enmities%20and%20self-righteous%20pieties%2C%20apparently%20impervious%20to%20shame%2C%20this%20discourse%20has%20systematically%20eliminated%20all%20the%20layered%20complexity%20that%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20stories%20bring%20to%20our%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOld%20or%20young%2C%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20Batta%20often%20finds%20himself%20playing%20a%20dubious%20role%20in%20both%20his%20private%20and%20his%20public%20life.%20Regardless%20of%20whether%20the%20story%20centres%20around%20hostility%20between%20father%20and%20son%20(as%20in%20%E2%80%98Curfew%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98A%20Late%20Winter%E2%80%99)%2C%20or%20around%20a%20young%20man%20desperately%20seeking%20recognition%20and%20success%20(as%20in%20%E2%80%98Twins%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Dogs%E2%80%99)%2C%20or%20indeed%2C%20any%20other%20theme%2C%20the%20reader%20is%20always%20conscious%20that%20there%20is%20something%20else%20impinging%20on%20the%20situation%2C%20bloating%20and%20contorting%20it.%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20skill%20lies%20in%20never%20attempting%20to%20define%20this%20%E2%80%9Csomething%20else.%E2%80%9D%20Like%20his%20protagonists%2C%20who%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20most%20important%20things%20cannot%20be%20spoken%2C%20he%20stages%20this%20weight%20as%20a%20natural%20phenomenon%3A%20the%20weather%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20cold%2C%20the%20snow%2C%20the%20wind%2C%20the%20rain%2C%20the%20sun%2C%20the%20heat%E2%80%A6those%20immutable%20forces%20to%20which%20the%20fragile%20human%20body%20must%20always%20adapt%20lest%20it%20perish%20%E2%80%93%20these%20become%20emblematic%20of%20something%20peculiar%20to%20Kashmir.%20Kaul%20writes%20as%20if%20what%20oppresses%20Kashmiris%20is%20no%20longer%20something%20historical%2C%20human%20and%20contingent%2C%20but%20something%20irrevocable%20and%20unyielding.%20Yet%20even%20as%20he%20writes%20in%20this%20way%2C%20he%20knows%20the%20duplicity%20of%20doing%20so.%20Yes%2C%20let%20us%20blame%20the%20weather%2C%20he%20says%20ironically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20consider%2C%20for%20example%2C%20%E2%80%98A%20Song%20of%20Despair%E2%80%99%20from%20the%20collection%20%3Cem%3EHaalas%20Chhu%20Rotul%20%3C%2Fem%3E(1985).%20The%20story%20mocks%20a%20generation%20that%20prided%20itself%20on%20breaking%20traditional%20conventions%2C%20that%20questioned%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20father%20and%20everything%20that%20such%20authority%20represents%2C%20but%20that%2C%20over%20time%2C%20moulded%20itself%20in%20exactly%20the%20same%20image%20of%20the%20father%20it%20had%20earlier%20resisted.%20The%20narrator%2C%20presumably%20a%20young%20man%2C%20recounts%20how%2C%20perched%20on%20his%20windowsill%20on%20a%20hot%20summer%20night%2C%20he%20watched%20a%20series%20of%20scenes%20unfold%20in%20a%20house%20across%20the%20street.%20As%20he%20recounts%20what%20he%20saw%2C%20he%20intersperses%20his%20observations%20with%20recollections%20of%20the%20past.%20By%20the%20time%20we%20reach%20the%20conclusion%2C%20we%20know%20that%20this%20is%20not%20just%20a%20story%20about%20Sri%20Kak%20Tikoo%2C%20Kishan%20Chand%20and%20Roop%20Ji%3B%20that%20it%20has%20assumed%20allegorical%20proportions%20for%20the%20narrator%20himself%20during%20the%20very%20act%20of%20narration%3B%20and%20that%20what%20oppresses%20him%20is%20the%20relentless%20hold%20of%20caste%20and%20religious%20prejudice%2C%20the%20inevitable%20return%20of%20the%20unyielding%20father%2C%20and%20above%20all%2C%20his%20impotent%20rage%20against%20a%20political%20class%20that%20cynically%20repeats%20precisely%20what%20it%20had%20once%20defied.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDefiance%20and%20transgression%20appear%20to%20him%20in%20retrospect%20as%20nothing%20but%20self-serving%20claims%20to%20power.%20Yet%20none%20of%20this%20can%20be%20explicitly%20articulated%20or%20acknowledged.%20Instead%2C%20this%20is%20all%20the%20narrator%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20felt%20as%20if%20I%20would%20scream.%20%5B.%20.%20.%5DThe%20night%20had%20begun%20to%20fade%2C%20but%20my%20restlessness%20had%20not.%20Usually%2C%20if%20I%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20sleep%20through%20the%20night%2C%20I%20would%20at%20least%20close%20my%20eyes%20at%20dawn.%20But%20tonight%20sleep%20was%20certainly%20upset%20with%20me%2C%20hiding%20far%20away.%20The%20heat%2C%20and%20humidity%20too%2C%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20ebbed.%20Summers%20are%20like%20this%3A%20the%20days%20burn%20you%20and%20the%20nights%20boil%20you%3B%20the%20evenings%20suffocate%20you%20and%20the%20mornings%20bring%20no%20relief.%E2%80%9D%20The%20cyclical%20return%20of%20the%20unendurable%20is%20thus%20transposed%20on%20to%20the%20weather%20%E2%80%93%20the%20extreme%2C%20relentless%2C%20exceptional%20weather%20of%20Kashmir.%20If%20one%20detects%20irony%20here%20%E2%80%93%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20gentle%20mockery%20of%20the%20narrator%E2%80%99s%20self-deception%20or%20self-protection%20%E2%80%93%20this%20irony%20nevertheless%20remains%20enmeshed%20in%20despair.%20We%20are%20aware%20that%20the%20story%20sings%20not%20just%20Khan%20Sahib%E2%80%99s%20or%20the%20narrator%E2%80%99s%2C%20but%20also%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%2C%20song%20of%20despair.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22There%20Is%20No%20Real%20Dislike%20for%20Cats%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20Art%20History%20Says%20as%20Much%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fart-history-cats-bn-goswamy-indian-cat%5C%22%3EThere%20Is%20No%20Real%20Dislike%20for%20Cats%20in%20India%20%E2%80%93%20Art%20History%20Says%20as%20Much%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EQuotidian%20encounters%2C%20insults%20and%20conversations%20assume%20an%20epic%20proportion%20in%20another%20story%20from%20the%20same%201985%20collection%2C%20a%20story%20titled%20%E2%80%98That%20Which%20We%20Cannot%20Speak%20Of%E2%80%99.%20The%20Kashmiri%20Pandit%20who%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20deceive%20himself%20understands%20very%20well%20that%20what%20appears%20as%20unprovoked%20aggression%20on%20the%20part%20of%20working%20class%20Muslims%20is%20at%20least%20partly%20produced%20by%20an%20enduring%20pact%20among%20educated%2C%20middle-class%20Muslims%20and%20Hindus.%20The%20obscenity%20of%20this%20pact%2C%20which%20silently%20reserves%20and%20distributes%20resources%20within%20its%20limited%20circle%2C%20cannot%20escape%20those%20kept%20outside%20the%20circle.%20(Indeed%2C%20one%20should%20pay%20attention%20to%20the%20entire%20system%20of%20front%20rows%20and%20back%20rows%2C%20front%20doors%20and%20back%20doors%2C%20those%20let%20in%20and%20those%20kept%20out%2C%20that%20structures%20many%20of%20these%20stories).%20The%20narrator%20of%20this%20story%20is%20aware%20of%20this%2C%20and%20yet%20he%20is%20unable%20to%20plumb%20the%20depths%20of%20his%20own%20aversion%20to%20the%20barber%20Magga%2C%20who%2C%20by%20the%20sheer%20force%20of%20his%20aggression%2C%20pushes%20the%20narrator%20to%20confront%20his%20own%20corruption%2C%20as%20well%20as%20that%20of%20his%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20story%20progresses%2C%20we%20descend%20deeper%20and%20deeper%20into%20a%20thicket%20of%20compromises%20and%20spite%20%E2%80%93%20a%20web%20of%20negotiation%20interwoven%20with%20a%20web%20of%20mutual%20suspicion.%20Thus%20the%20very%20act%20of%20storytelling%20is%20presented%20here%20as%20one%20that%20inevitably%20betrays%20secrets%20that%20the%20narrator%20would%20rather%20have%20withheld%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20act%20of%20telling%2C%20%E2%80%9Cblunders%E2%80%9D%20are%20made%20and%20what%20should%20be%20hidden%20is%20clumsily%20brought%20to%20light.%20But%20what%20is%20brought%20to%20light%20is%20never%20an%20explanation%20or%20a%20meaningful%20revelation%2C%20only%20more%20and%20more%20stories%20%E2%80%93%20a%20sequence%20of%20related%2C%20interconnected%20shapes%20each%20of%20which%20withhold%20their%20final%20meaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20299px)%2085vw%2C%20299px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19165647%2Fhkkaul3.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22299%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19165647%2Fhkkaul3.jpeg%20849w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19165647%2Fhkkaul3-228x300.jpeg%20228w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19165647%2Fhkkaul3-779x1024.jpeg%20779w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685429%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22393%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EHari%20Krishna%20Kaul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20often-cited%201936%20essay%20on%20the%20storyteller%2C%20the%20German%20philosopher%20Walter%20Benjamin%20presented%20us%20with%20a%20paradox.%20He%20wrote%20that%20storytelling%20has%20declined%20because%20our%20ability%20to%20communicate%20our%20experience%2C%20which%20is%20of%20the%20essence%20in%20storytelling%2C%20has%20waned.%20Yet%20it%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20understand%20what%20Benjamin%20means%20by%20such%20communication%2C%20since%20the%20stories%20to%20which%20he%20refers%20as%20models%20are%20those%20that%20do%20not%20in%20fact%20communicate%20a%20meaning%20or%20a%20moral%20to%20the%20reader.%20What%20they%20communicate%2C%20instead%2C%20is%20a%20plot%20without%20any%20attempt%20at%20psychologisation%2C%20so%20that%20the%20listener%20is%20provoked%20to%20ruminate%2C%20to%20puzzle%20over%20what%20has%20happened.%20The%20function%20of%20stories%2C%20Benjamin%20seems%20to%20say%2C%20is%20to%20bring%20us%20closer%20to%20the%20enigmas%20of%20human%20history%20%E2%80%93%20enigmas%20of%20which%20death%20remains%20both%20the%20limit%20and%20the%20custodian.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Hari%20Krishna%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20stories%20often%20withhold%20explanation%2C%20this%20does%20not%20only%20render%20the%20stories%20more%20memorable%2C%20more%20capable%20of%20being%20deeply%20absorbed%20by%20the%20listener%20or%20the%20reader%2C%20as%20Benjamin%20suggests%20in%20his%20essay.%20It%20also%20lets%20the%20reader%20be%20absorbed%20precisely%20by%20their%20stifling%20insularity.%20That%20is%20perhaps%20why%20these%20stories%20make%20no%20attempt%20to%20breach%20this%20insularity%20by%20explicitly%20connecting%20the%20Kashmir%20they%20describe%20with%20a%20wider%20geopolitical%20domain.%20By%20the%20time%20we%20read%20the%20last%20stories%20of%20the%20collection%2C%20from%20a%20collection%20published%20in%202001%2C%20it%20becomes%20apparent%20that%20the%20claustrophobic%20insularity%20that%20some%20of%20the%20other%20stories%20obliquely%20critique%20has%20itself%20become%2C%20for%20those%20exiled%20from%20it%2C%20a%20lost%20and%20desired%20object.%20This%20may%20be%20why%20such%20insularity%20must%20be%20kept%20intact%2C%20at%20least%20for%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20generation%20of%20Pandits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20translations%20of%20fiction%20are%20almost%20always%20a%20labour%20of%20love%2C%20in%20reading%20translations%20one%20rarely%20feels%20that%20the%20translation%20itself%20is%20a%20gift%20to%20the%20original.%20By%20this%20I%20mean%2C%20not%20that%20the%20translation%20extends%20the%20life%20of%20the%20original%2C%20or%20brings%20to%20it%20a%20new%20readership%20%E2%80%93%20that%2C%20of%20course%2C%20most%20translations%20do.%20I%20mean%2C%20rather%2C%20that%20the%20translation%20itself%20somehow%20intervenes%20in%2C%20rearranges%2C%20%3Cem%3Eaddresses%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20very%20anxieties%20that%20traverse%20the%20original.%20Without%20offering%20any%20facile%20hope%20or%20resolution%20to%20the%20loss%20or%20despair%20of%20which%20these%20stories%20speak%20%E2%80%93%20indeed%2C%20precisely%20by%20staying%20close%20to%20this%20despair%20(%3Cem%3EFor%20Now%2C%20It%20Is%20Night%3C%2Fem%3E)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20translation%20is%20nevertheless%20able%20to%20enact%20and%20hence%20%3Cem%3Egenerate%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20kind%20of%20community%20that%20only%20appears%20as%20an%20absence%20in%20these%20stories%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20a%20community%20of%20Kashmiris%2C%20both%20Muslim%20and%20Hindu%2C%20who%2C%20even%20if%20they%20might%20have%20left%20Kashmir%2C%20have%20abandoned%20neither%20Kashmir%20nor%20those%20who%2C%20like%20Kaul%2C%20kept%20attentive%20vigil%20over%20its%20vicissitudes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22%E2%80%98The%20Absent%20Color%E2%80%99%3A%20Mapping%20the%20Contours%20of%20%E2%80%98A%20Nil%E2%80%99%20World%2C%20a%20Trial%20for%20Imagination%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-absent-color-mapping-the-contours-of-a-nil-world-a-trial-for-imagination%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20Absent%20Color%E2%80%99%3A%20Mapping%20the%20Contours%20of%20%E2%80%98A%20Nil%E2%80%99%20World%2C%20a%20Trial%20for%20Imagination%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20much%20more%20that%20could%20be%20said%20about%20these%20stories%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%2C%20about%20the%20wry%20humour%20that%20leavens%20them%2C%20the%20spirit%20of%20Kafka%20that%20sometimes%20seems%20to%20flash%20across%20a%20story%2C%20the%20impress%20of%20the%20great%20Akhtar%20Mohiuddin%20on%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20writing%2C%20and%20the%20rigorous%20economy%20of%20the%20translation.%20There%20are%20many%20questions%20I%20puzzled%20over%20as%20I%20read%3A%20was%20Premchand%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Kafan%E2%80%99%20on%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20mind%20when%20he%20wrote%20%E2%80%98The%20Mourners%E2%80%99%3F%20Are%20these%20stories%20taught%20in%20Kashmir%20today%2C%20and%20if%20so%2C%20how%20are%20they%20taught%3F%20What%20do%20contemporary%20Kashmiri%20readers%20make%20of%20the%20thinly%20veiled%20allusions%20to%20homosexuality%3F%20Had%20Kaul%20read%20Ismat%20Chughtai%3F%20What%20were%20some%20of%20the%20most%20difficult%20phrases%20and%20words%20to%20translate%20into%20English%3F%20Other%20readers%20will%20doubtless%20ponder%20over%20their%20own%20questions%20as%20they%20read%20these%20stories.%20I%20only%20hope%20that%20there%20will%20be%20many%20such%20readers%2C%20for%20the%20labour%20of%20love%20that%20has%20produced%20this%20beautiful%20translation%20will%20find%20fertile%20ground%20only%20if%20we%20read%2C%20reflect%20upon%2C%20and%20in%20turn%20translate%20these%20stories%20into%20our%20own%20thought-worlds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESimona%20Sawhney%20teaches%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20Humanities%20and%20Social%20Sciences%20at%20IIT%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700394333000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19170000%2F5594744044_9daabf434d_k.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fhari-krishna-kaul-stories%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20translation%20of%20Hari%20Krishna%20Kaul%E2%80%99s%20stories%2C%20'For%20Now%20It%20Is%20Night'%2C%20brings%20out%20the%20different%20shapes%20of%20loneliness%20in%20Kashmiri%20Pandits'%20lives.%22%2C