while%20in%20Vail%2C%2040%20miles%20west%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Fhome-values%2F41448%2Fvail-co%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eit%20was%20%241.6%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow.%20Prices%20for%20housing%20and%20other%20essentials%2C%20which%20have%20skyrocketed%20since%202019%2C%20are%20a%20turn-off%20for%20the%20very%20workers%20who%20keep%20the%20resorts%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20retail%20shops%20running.%20But%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reports%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Freal-estate%2Fhow-two-of-americas-wealthiest-vacation-spots-are-fighting-to-free-up-homes-for-locals-4a399cf3%3Fmod%3Dhp_featst_pos4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVail%20is%20trying%20a%20relatively%20new%20tactic%3A%20paying%20homeowners%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20exchange%20for%20a%20promise%20that%20they'll%20rent%20to%20local%20workers%20rather%20than%20deep-pocketed%20tourists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20popular%20vacation%20spots%20across%20the%20country%20are%20coming%20up%20with%20other%20ways%20to%20carve%20out%20housing%20for%20locals.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcities-fighting-airbnbs-with-regulations-for-short-term-rentals-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESome%2C%20like%20Aspen%2C%20are%20limiting%20short-term%20rentals%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20hopes%20that%20that%20housing%20will%20be%20used%20for%20workers%20signing%20year-long%20leases%20instead%3B%20others%2C%20like%20Big%20Sky%2C%20Montana%2C%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kbzk.com%2Fnews%2Flocal-news%2Fnew-affordable-housing-coming-to-big-sky-as-early-as-next-winter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ebuilding%20affordable%20housing%20specifically%20for%20workers%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EVail's%20housing-for-locals%20program%20is%20promising%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Freal-estate%2Fhow-two-of-americas-wealthiest-vacation-spots-are-fighting-to-free-up-homes-for-locals-4a399cf3%3Fmod%3Dhp_featst_pos4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Journal%20article%20explores%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20Vail's%20director%20of%20housing%2C%20George%20Ruther%2C%20is%20exploring%20innovative%20solutions%20to%20the%20worker%20housing%20crisis.%20Case%20in%20point%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vail.gov%2Fgovernment%2Fdepartments%2Fhousing%2Fvailindeed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%202017-launched%20program%20called%20inDEED%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20uses%20town%20money%20to%20buy%20a%20stake%20in%20local%20homes.%20The%20one%20condition%20to%20get%20the%20cash%3F%20That%20the%20owners%20rent%20them%20out%20to%20local%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20homeowner%20accepts%2C%20the%20town%20implements%20a%20deed%20restriction%20that%20requires%20the%20house%20to%20be%20occupied%20by%20at%20least%20one%20person%20who%20works%20an%20annual%20average%20of%2030%20hours%20or%20more%20a%20week%20in%20the%20county%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huduser.gov%2Fportal%2Fhome.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20description%20of%20the%20program%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Development's%20Office%20of%20Policy%20Development%20and%20Research.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20essentially%20prevents%20the%20home%20from%20becoming%20a%20vacation%20rental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypical%20deed-restriction%20payments%20are%2020%25%20of%20the%20market%20value%20of%20the%20property%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Journal%2C%20and%20Ruther%20said%20he's%20not%20concerned%20if%20the%20homeowners%20themselves%20are%20locals%20or%20out-of-towners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20care%20who%20owns%20the%20property.%20I%20only%20care%20who%20lives%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Ruther%20told%20the%20Journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20the%20town%20has%20spent%20%2417%20million%20for%20at%20least%20200%20restrictions%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Journal.%20Vail%20is%20also%20financing%20construction%20on%20294%20deed-restricted%20apartments%20in%20a%20new%20housing%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20has%20not%20been%20foolproof%2C%20however.%20The%20Journal%20reported%20that%20a%20compliance%20sweep%20last%20February%20uncovered%20some%20deed-restricted%20homes%20violating%20their%20terms%20and%20not%20renting%20to%20locals.%20The%20town%20got%20a%20%241%20million%20settlement%20that%20it%20will%20use%20to%20snap%20up%20new%20deed%20restrictions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vaildaily.com%2Fnews%2Fvail-reaches-1-million-settlement-with-altus-vail-over-deed-restriction-violations%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20local%20newspaper%20Vail%20Daily.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAffordable%20housing%20is%20essential%20for%20Vail%20employers%20and%20employees%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESolving%20the%20ski-town%20housing%20crisis%20is%20crucial%20for%20employers%20like%20Vail%20restaurant%20owner%20Paul%20Anders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20Business%20Insider%20earlier%20this%20year%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvail-colorado-affordable-housing-employees-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20worker%20exodus%20from%20Vail%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20forced%20his%20business%20to%20stop%20offering%20lunch%20some%20days.%20Plus%2C%20Anders%20and%20his%20business%20partners%20have%20bought%20or%20leased%2011%20apartments%20for%20workers%20over%20the%20years.%20As%20of%20February%2C%20he%20housed%2030%20of%20his%20employees%2C%20nearly%20one-fifth%20of%20his%20staff%2C%20in%20dwellings%20he%20offers%20at%20below-market%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHousing%20is%20the%20single%20most%20impactful%20factor%20for%20every%20business%20in%20Vail%2C%26quot%3B%20Anders%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Allison%20Weibel%2C%20who%20paid%20%24600%20a%20month%20for%20a%20room%20in%20a%20ski-resort-subsidized%20four-bedroom%20apartment%20when%20she%20was%20working%20part-time%20as%20a%20ski%20instructor.%20But%20switching%20to%20teaching%20full-time%20forced%20her%20to%20move%2030%20minutes%20away%20to%20find%20a%20home%20she%20could%20afford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTeachers%2C%20like%20myself%2C%20want%20to%20stay%20here%20in%20the%20community%2C%20but%20doing%20so%20requires%20the%20stability%20that%20homeownership%20can%20offer%2C%26quot%3B%20Weibel%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvail-colorado-affordable-worker-housing-ski-towns-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700393882000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6555431522cf74a573982c95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvail-colorado-affordable-worker-housing-ski-towns-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ski-town%20employees%20can't%20afford%20to%20live%20where%20they%20work.%20Vail%20is%20paying%20homeowners%20to%20rent%20to%20locals%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20tiny%20progress%20for%20a%20big%20problem.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dlatu%40insider.com%20(Dan%20Latu)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvail-colorado-affordable-worker-housing-ski-towns-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watching%20Ukraine%20burn%20through%20ammo%20fighting%20Russia%20has%20the%20US%20Army%20rethinking%20how%20much%20it%20really%20needs%20for%20when%20war%20breaks%20out%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20artillery%20soldiers%20troops%20Bakhmut%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557c07122cf74a573999070%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20artillery%20unit%20fires%20toward%20Russian%20positions%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Bakhmut%20on%20December%2030%2C%202022.%3Cp%3ESAMEER%20AL-DOUMY%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBoth%20sides%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20have%20burned%20through%20insane%20amounts%20of%20ammo%2C%20straining%20stockpiles%20globally.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20war%20has%20prompted%20the%20US%20Army%20to%20rethink%20how%20much%20it%20should%20be%20producing%20and%20stockpiling%2C%20both%20for%20itself%20and%20its%20allies.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20US%20official%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20Army%20is%20both%20ramping%20up%20production%20and%20modernizing%20its%20process.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20burning%20through%20ammo%20at%20astonishing%20rates%2C%20the%20US%20Army%20says%20it's%20rethinking%20what%20it%20needs%20for%20a%20potential%20large-scale%20future%20fight.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20with%20production%2C%20particularly%20of%20155mm%20artillery%20shells%2C%20ramping%20up%2C%20the%20Army%20is%20also%20looking%20at%20%3Cstrong%3Ehow%20to%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20modernize%20its%20ongoing%20manufacturing%20and%20stockpiles%20%E2%80%94%20both%20to%20continue%20supporting%20allies%20like%20Ukraine%20and%20Israel%2C%20as%20well%20as%20have%20enough%20ammo%20should%20the%20US%20find%20itself%20in%20a%20high-intensity%20conflict%20of%20its%20own%2C%20especially%20against%20a%20major%20military%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20is%20looking%20very%20closely%20at%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20how%20munitions%20are%20used%20to%20inform%20our%20decisions%20regarding%20munitions%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20Douglas%20R.%20Bush%2C%20the%20assistant%20secretary%20of%20the%20Army%20for%20Acquisition%2C%20Logistics%20and%20Technology%2C%20explained%20to%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BRecognizing%20the%20use%20of%20large%20quantities%20of%20artillery%20on%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20conflict%2C%20the%20Army%20is%20investing%20to%20better%20prepare%20for%20potential%20conflict%20and%20to%20support%20Ukraine%20as%20they%20continue%20to%20fight%20for%20their%20freedom.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20those%20efforts%20are%20ambitious%20short-term%20goals%2C%20like%20upping%20155mm%20production%20from%20just%20shy%20of%2030%2C000%20shells%20a%20month%20right%20now%20to%20a%20massive%20100%2C000%20shells%20a%20month%20by%20the%20end%20of%202025.%20But%20another%20larger%2C%20more%20long-term%20effort%20appears%20to%20be%20securing%20a%20stronger%20supply%20chain%20and%20more%20constant%20manufacturing%20of%20munitions%20both%20domestically%20and%20with%20the%20support%20of%20US%20partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Army%20began%20making%20investments%20over%20a%20year%20ago%20in%20our%20organic%20and%20commercial%20industrial%20base%20to%20accelerate%20production%20and%20improve%20capacity%20for%20155mm%20and%20other%20munitions%2C%20in%20order%20to%20meet%20demands%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20allied%20partners%2C%20and%20US%20stockpile%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20Bush%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20at%20the%20timeline%2C%20those%20investments%20appear%20to%20have%20come%20after%20Russia%20launched%20its%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20and%20after%20both%20sides%20began%20expending%20tremendous%20amounts%20of%20ammunition%20attempting%20to%20batter%20the%20opposing%20army%2C%20launching%20enough%20artillery%20shells%20to%20severely%20strain%20stockpiles%20worldwide%C2%A0and%20even%20push%20partners%20to%20send%20over%20controversial%20weapons%20like%20cluster%20munitions%20to%20slow%20the%20ammo%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224435%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukrainian%20artillery%20fires%20towards%20the%20frontline%20during%20heavy%20fighting%20amid%20Russia's%20attack%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20near%20Bakhmut%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20April%2013%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64500eeb74e9330018efc58d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222857%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUkrainian%20artillery%20fires%20towards%20the%20frontline%20during%20heavy%20fighting%20amid%20Russia's%20attack%20on%20Ukraine%2C%20near%20Bakhmut%2C%20Ukraine%2C%20April%2013%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FKai%20Pfaffenbach%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20weapons%20and%20systems%2C%20such%20as%20Storm%20Shadow%2FSCALP%20long-range%20cruise%20missiles%2C%20first-person%20view%20(FPV)%20drones%2C%20Russian%20Kinzhal%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20and%20Western%20tanks%20like%20Leopard%20and%20Challenger%2C%20have%2C%20at%20some%20point%20or%20another%2C%20had%20their%20moment%20in%20the%20war%20thus%20far.%20But%20this%20conflict%20appears%20to%20be%20marked%20most%20by%20artillery%20and%20has%20offered%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20its%20role%20in%20future%20conflicts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20relies%20heavily%20on%20systems%20like%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-war-shows-towed-artillery-more-vulnerable-in-future-2023-10%5C%22%3Etowed%20155mm%20and%20105mm%20howitzers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20rocket%20artillery%20assets%20like%20the%20High-Mobility%20Artillery%20Rocket%20System%20(HIMARS).%20pummeling%20Russian%20forces%20miles%20away%20and%20devastating%20advancing%20troops%20and%20vehicles%2C%20as%20well%20as%20command%2C%20control%2C%20and%20logistics.%20It's%20heavily%20relied%20on%20the%20US%20and%20NATO%20allies%20for%20its%20supply%20of%20ammo%2C%20and%20many%20Western%20nations%20have%20had%20their%20stockpiles%20stressed%20by%20the%20provision%20of%20this%20vital%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20Russia%20has%20often%20expended%20ammunition%20at%20even%20higher%20rates%20than%20the%20Ukrainians%2C%20who%20often%20speak%20of%20rationing%20their%20ammo%20consumption.%20Even%20in%20the%20face%20of%20heavy%20Western%20sanctions%20and%20a%20pariah%20status%20that%20have%20severely%20limited%20its%20ammo%20production%2C%20it's%20still%20been%20able%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-ammunition-manufacturing-ukraine-west-officials-2023-9%5C%22%3Ebolster%20its%20stockpiles%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20has%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-desperate-need-for-weapons-ukraine-win-for-north-korea-2023-9%5C%22%3Esought%20out%20foreign%20partners%20for%20munitions%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Back%20in%20September%2C%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20hosted%20North%20Korean%20leader%20Kim%20Kong%20Un%20for%20a%20meeting%20on%20North%20Korean%20artillery.%20The%20result%20was%20an%20arms%20deal%20of%20sorts%20%E2%80%94%20Russia%20got%20ammo%2C%20while%20North%20Korea%20likely%20got%20food%20and%20petroleum%20products.%C2%A0The%20exact%20details%20of%20that%20deal%20are%20unclear%2C%20but%20there%20are%20indications%20North%20Korean%20ammunition%20has%20already%20arrived%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20US%2C%20Ukraine's%20biggest%20single-nation%20donor%2C%20the%20constant%20bombardment%20from%20both%20sides%20has%20apparently%20been%20eye-opening%2C%20offering%20insights%20into%20not%20only%20how%20much%20artillery%20ammunition%20Ukraine%20needs%20to%20sustain%20its%20war%20effort%2C%20but%20also%20how%20much%20ammo%20the%20US%20may%20need%20in%20a%20future%20fight.%C2%A0It's%20also%20offered%20lessons%20into%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20conflict%20has%20allowed%20the%20Army%20to%20recognize%20that%20challenge%20of%20implementing%20multiple%20initiatives%20to%20expand%20industrial%20capacity%20without%20disrupting%20current%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20Bush%20told%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228476%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20remains%20of%20artillery%20shells%20and%20missiles%20including%20cluster%20munitions%20are%20stored%20on%20December%2018%2C%202022%20in%20Toretsk%2C%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64a820ca8ed31300199e1137%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225656%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20remains%20of%20artillery%20shells%20and%20missiles%20including%20cluster%20munitions%20are%20stored%20on%20December%2018%2C%202022%20in%20Toretsk%2C%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Pierre%20Crom%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20roundtable%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20Bush%20told%20journalists%20the%20US%20was%20expanding%20and%20modernizing%20its%20ammo%20capacity%2C%20making%20a%20variety%20of%20new%20munitions%20to%20bolster%20its%20stockpiles%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20critical%20investments%20that%26quot%3B%20are%20%26quot%3Bpart%20of%20the%20supplemental%20requests%20that%20builds%20additional%20capacity%20in%20our%20industrial%20base.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20primary%20focus%20appears%20to%20be%20on%20155mm%20shells%2C%20which%20Ukraine%20has%20burned%20through%20in%20artillery%20duels%20with%20the%20Russians%20and%20the%20US%20has%20had%20to%20find%20%26quot%3Bcreative%20ways%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20to%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Bush%2C%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20war%2C%20the%20US%20was%20at%2014%2C000%20shells%20a%20month%20and%20has%20ramped%20up%20to%20its%20current%20rate%20of%2028%2C000%20a%20month.%20It's%20looking%20to%20make%2036%2C000%20monthly%20by%20early%202024%20and%20then%20skyrocketing%20production%20to%2060%2C000%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20fiscal%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20end%20of%202025%2C%20Bush%20said%2C%20the%20Army%20is%20projecting%20100%2C000%20a%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20staggering%20number%20but%20a%20lot%20has%20to%20come%20together%20to%20make%20those%20numbers%20a%20reality.%20For%20one%2C%20the%20Army%20plans%20to%20increase%20manufacturing%20abilities%20at%20existing%20government%20facilities%20while%20building%20new%20domestic%20sites%20with%20commercial%20partners.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20the%20Army%2C%20any%20increase%20is%20a%20net%20positive.%20%26quot%3BGetting%20to%20those%20higher%20production%20rates%20is%20kind%20of%20a%20win-win%2C%26quot%3B%20Bush%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20support%20Ukraine%20or%20Israel%20more%2C%20but%20it%20also%20means%20that%20we%20can%20rebuild%20our%20stocks%20much%20faster%20than%20if%20we%20don't%20make%20those%20investments.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20production%20still%20ramping%20up%20and%20both%20Ukraine%20and%20Israel%20in%20conflicts%2C%20the%20US%20may%20find%20supporting%20them%20both%20increasingly%20challenging.%20On%20Friday%2C%20Ukrainian%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%20said%20the%20supply%20of%20artillery%20to%20Ukraine%20had%20slowed%20down%20since%20Israel%20began%20its%20war%20on%20Hamas%20after%20the%20group's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-declares-state-of-war-hamas-launches-massive-surprise-attack-2023-10%5C%22%3Emulti-front%20surprise%20terrorist%20attacks%20last%20month%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20in%20that%20roundtable%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20Bush%20denied%20any%20shells%20intended%20for%20Ukraine%20had%20been%20given%20to%20Israel%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNothing%20that%20was%20being%20shipped%20to%20Ukraine%20got%20redirected%2C%26quot%3B%20Bush%20said.%20Instead%2C%20he%20noted%2C%20munitions%20had%20been%20moved%20out%20of%20US%20stocks%20in%20Israel%20and%20given%20directly%20to%20them.%20He%20said%20the%20US%20had%20sent%20ammo%20from%20its%20own%20stockpile%20to%20Israel%20as%20well%20but%20did%20not%20give%20an%20exact%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-rethinking-how-much-ammunition-it-needs-ukraine-war-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700393401000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6557bc2536d588dc55d29420%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fww