at%20has%20left%2041%20lives%20hanging%20by%20the%20thread.%20A%20part%20of%20the%20under-construction%20tunnel%20to%20connect%20Uttarkashi%20and%20Yamunotri%20collapsed%20last%20Sunday%20after%20a%20landslide%2C%20trapping%20the%20workers.%20This%20tunnel%20is%20part%20of%20the%20centre's%20ambitious%20Char%20Dham%20project.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20week%2C%20repeated%20attempts%20to%20rescue%20the%20workers%20have%20failed%20owing%20to%20several%20challenges%2C%20including%20the%20topography%20and%20the%20nature%20of%20rocks%20in%20the%20area.%20The%20workers%20are%20being%20provided%20food%2C%20water%20and%20oxygen%20supply%20as%20rescue%20teams%20work%20overtime%20for%20a%20breakthrough.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20the%20media%2C%20Mr%20Gadkari%20said%20the%20priority%20is%20to%20keep%20the%20workers%20alive.%20%26quot%3BIf%20the%20auger%20machine%20works%20properly%2C%20we%20will%20be%20able%20to%20reach%20them%20in%20the%20next%202-2.5%20days.%20Roads%20are%20being%20made%20by%20BRO%20(Border%20Roads%20Organisition)%20to%20bring%20in%20special%20machines.%20Several%20machines%20have%20arrived%20here.%20Two%20auger%20machines%20are%20currently%20working%20to%20carry%20out%20rescue%20operations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20said%20several%20machines%20have%20arrived%20at%20the%20spot%20and%20two%20are%20currently%20working%20to%20rescue%20the%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Minister%20Dhami%20told%20news%20agency%20ANI%20that%20his%20government%20to%20ready%20to%20provide%20help%20to%20the%20rescue%20agencies.%C2%A0%26quot%3BSaving%20everyone's%20life%20is%20our%20first%20priority.%20For%20this%2C%20the%20state%20government%20is%20ready%20to%20give%20all%20the%20help%20required%20to%20all%20the%20agencies.%20I%20will%20pray%20to%20God%20that%20they%20get%20rescued%20sooner%2C%20as%20their%20trouble%20is%20increasing%20with%20each%20passing%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETeams%20from%20multiple%20agencies%20are%20at%20the%20spot%20for%20the%20challenging%20rescue%20operation.%20These%20include%20officials%20from%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Office%20(PMO).%20%26quot%3BThe%20experts%20agree%20that%20instead%20of%20working%20on%20one%20plan%2C%20we%20should%20work%20simultaneously%20on%20five%20plans%20to%20reach%20the%20trapped%20workers%20at%20the%20earliest%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bhaskar%20Khulbe%2C%20former%20advisor%20to%20the%20Prime%20Minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Khulbe%20said%20the%20workers%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20rescued%20in%20four-five%20days.%20%26quot%3BBut%20if%20the%20gods%20are%20kind%20enough%2C%20it%20could%20happen%20even%20earlier%20than%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700387100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fnvsb6rco_uttarakhand-tunnel_625x300_19_November_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtarakhand-tunnel-uttarkashi-nitin-gadkari-if-machine-works-properly-nitin-gadkaris-tunnel-rescue-timeline-4586957%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Rescue%20teams%20may%20reach%20the%2041%20workers%20stuck%20inside%20an%20Uttarakhand%20tunnel%20for%20over%20170%20hours%20in%20the%20next%20two%20days%20if%20the%20auger%20machine%20drilling%20into%20the%20debris%20block%20works%20properly%2C%20Union%20Minister%20for%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways%20Nitin%20Gadkari%20said%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtarakhand-tunnel-uttarkashi-nitin-gadkari-if-machine-works-properly-nitin-gadkaris-tunnel-rescue-timeline-4586957%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtarakhand-tunnel-uttarkashi-nitin-gadkari-if-machine-works-properly-nitin-gadkaris-tunnel-rescue-timeline-4586957%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Futtarakhand-tunnel-uttarkashi-nitin-gadkari-if-machine-works-properly-nitin-gadkaris-tunnel-rescue-timeline-4586957%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Assembly%20Polls%20Are%20a%20Litmus%20Test%20for%20Congress%20and%20Rahul%20Gandhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19150848%2FF_Ioh-sXMAAaoYX.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20processes%20and%20results%20of%20elections%20reflect%20institutional%20robustness%20and%20the%20resilience%20of%20parties%2C%20aside%20from%20the%20numbers%20in%20legislatures%2C%20and%20processes%20of%20power%20perpetuation%20and%20transfer.%20Equally%2C%20they%20show%20the%20endurance%20and%20innovativeness%20of%20the%20political%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20these%20perspectives%2C%20both%20India%E2%80%99s%20grand%20old%20party%20and%20its%20leader%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20have%20been%20on%20test%20for%20the%20past%20nine%20years.%C2%A0%20Striving%20with%20limited%20success%20against%20the%20Modi-Shah%20BJP%2C%20they%20are%20on%20test%20in%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Mizoram%2C%20Rajasthan%20and%20Telangana.%C2%A0%20Earlier%2C%20the%20Congress%20had%20a%20morale%20boosting%20victory%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20which%20was%20lost%20to%20%E2%80%98Operation%20Lotus%E2%80%99%20in%202019.%C2%A0%20The%20local%20leadership%2C%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%E2%80%99s%20mature%20handling%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%2C%20in%20that%20order%2C%20brought%20about%20the%20win.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20415px)%2085vw%2C%20415px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22415%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-300x248.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26081310%2FIMG_2711-1024x845.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681756%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22342%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20narrative%20has%20been%20dominated%20by%20the%20cult%20of%20Modi%2C%20Hindutva%20and%20economic%20freebies%20such%20as%20free%20electricity%20(courtesy%20Arvind%20Kejriwal)%2C%20free%20food%20grains%20for%20the%20poor%2C%20cash%20transfers%20to%20poor%20women%2C%20free%20bicycles%20and%20laptops%2C%20the%20revival%20of%20the%20Old%20Pension%20Scheme%2C%20loan%20waivers%2C%20subsidised%20fertiliser%20and%20enhanced%20MSP%20for%20farmers.%C2%A0%20A%20new%20dimension%20has%20been%20added%20with%20the%20caste%20census%20in%20Bihar%20and%20tweaked%20job%20quotas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20GOP%20has%20resolved%20the%20issue%20of%20a%20non-Nehru-Gandhi%20party%20president%20with%20the%20election%20of%20the%20shrewd%20and%20low-key%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge.%C2%A0%20It%20has%20changed%20its%20public%20perception%2C%20ending%20the%20uncertainty%20caused%20by%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20relinquishing%20the%20post%20in%20a%20huff%20in%202019%20and%20the%20return%20of%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20as%20interim%20president.%20Kharge%E2%80%99s%20organisational%20skills%20have%20been%20visible%20in%20Karnataka%20and%20Rajasthan.%20But%20the%20larger%20task%20of%20rebuilding%20the%20party%20district%20by%20district%2C%20state%20by%20state%2C%20needs%20gigantic%20steps.%20No%20wonder%2C%20busy%20with%20election-bound%20states%2C%20he%20is%20unable%20to%20attend%20to%20party%20issues%20countrywide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20continues%20to%20be%20projected%20as%20the%20leader%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20little%20room%20for%20others%20at%20the%20top.%C2%A0%20The%20official%20party%20website%20still%20has%20pictures%20of%20the%20three%20Gandhis%20%E2%80%93%20Rahul%2C%20Priyanka%20and%20Sonia%2C%20before%20that%20of%20Kharge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20highlights%20five%20issues%20%E2%80%93%20Farmers%20of%20India%2C%20Neighbourhood%20Lost%20(foreign%20policy)%2C%20Job%20Destruction%2C%20Demonetization%20and%20GST.%C2%A0%20Manifestos%20for%20the%20five%20poll-bound%20states%20are%20missing%20online.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20the%20poll%20manifestos%20released%20for%20three%20states%20do%20not%20project%20it%20as%20the%20party%20with%20a%20vision.%20It%20is%20fire-fighting%20with%20populism.%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20most%20challenging%20state%2C%20has%20made%20promises%20like%20cash%20transfers%20to%20women%20heads%20of%20families%2C%20laptops%20or%20tablets%20for%20college%20students%2C%20buying%20cow%20dung%20(sic)%2C%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20OPS%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20In%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20it%20promises%20a%20caste%20census%2C%20loan%20waiver%20to%20farmers%2C%20Rs%20500%20subsidy%20on%20gas%20cylinders%2C%20free%20education%20to%20students%20up%20to%20the%20postgrad%20level%2C%20free%20electricity%20up%20to%20200%20units%20and%20other%20subsidies.%20Such%20populist%20offers%20are%20also%20in%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20manifesto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20local%20variations%2C%20the%20Telangana%20and%20Mizoram%20manifestos%20are%20also%20full%20of%20populism.%C2%A0%20Telangana%20promises%2010%20grams%20of%20gold%20and%20Rs%201%20lakh%20financial%20assistance%20for%20the%20marriage%20of%20poor%20girls.%C2%A0%20Mizoram%20promises%20health%20insurance%20coverage%20up%20to%2015%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20still%20not%20clear%20if%20any%20of%20the%20manifestoes%2C%20on%20which%20state%20leaders%20have%20worked%20with%20Kharge%2C%20reflect%20Rahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20vision%2C%20too.%20Debuting%20in%20politics%20in%202004%2C%20his%20leadership%20record%20is%20sombre.%C2%A0%20In%202019%2C%20he%20contested%20from%20Kerala.%20apart%20from%20Amethi%2C%20which%20he%20lost.%20He%20abruptly%20resigned%20from%20the%20party%20presidency%20in%202019.%20His%20BJY%20was%20indeed%20a%20major%20initiative%20but%20by%20all%20accounts%2C%20it%20has%20had%20limited%20success%20and%20very%20little%20impact%20on%20the%20organisation.%20The%20coming%20elections%20would%20show%20if%20the%20BJY%20has%20established%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20shrugged%20off%20the%20%E2%80%98Pappu%E2%80%99%20image%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20media%20cell%20has%20projected%20at%20great%20cost%20since%202004%2C%20but%20his%20acceptability%20as%20the%20alternative%20national%20leader%20is%20untested.%20Even%20though%20lately%2C%20the%20GOP%20has%20reportedly%20collected%20comprehensive%20data%20on%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20socio-economic%20situation%2C%20his%20speeches%20rarely%20reflect%20those.%20Aping%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20Hindutva%2C%20he%20and%20his%20party%20leaders%20go%20to%20temples%2C%C2%A0%20and%20he%20allows%20his%20party%20leaders%20to%20court%20controversial%20seers%2C%20even%20build%20tall%20statues%20of%20the%20Hindu%20divinities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELately%2C%20beyond%20attacks%20on%20the%20Adani-Modi%20nexus%2C%20he%20has%20spoken%20aggressively%2C%20offering%20to%20emulate%20the%20caste%20census%20of%20Bihar%20in%20the%20poll-bound%20states.%20Describing%20the%20process%20as%20an%20X-ray%20or%20MRI%20of%20society%2C%20he%20aims%20to%20attract%20the%20OBC%20votes.%20He%20has%20pointedly%20highlighted%20that%20less%20than%200.5%25%20of%20secretary%20and%20joint%20secretary%20level%20officers%20in%20central%20government%20are%20OBC.%20He%20has%20promised%20to%20correct%20such%20anomalies%20if%20the%20Congress%20is%20elected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20he%20ought%20to%20spell%20out%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20policy%20perspective%20on%20education%2C%20employment%2C%20the%20misuse%20of%20institutions%20such%20as%20governor%20and%20reform%20of%20the%20highly%20politicised%20police%20and%20civil%20service.%20As%20a%20national%20leader%2C%20his%20perspective%20on%20foreign%20policy%20also%20needs%20clear%20expression.%20Obviously%2C%20even%20though%20he%20is%20more%20visible%20and%20has%20greater%20public%20acceptance%2C%20his%20advisors%20need%20to%20work%20on%20these%20aspects%20of%20his%20leadership%20persona.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedia%20reports%20have%20indicated%20internal%20contradictions%20within%20the%20BJP%2C%20governance%20deficit%20and%20corruption%20in%20BJP-ruled%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20may%20help%20the%20Congress%20to%20win%20at%20least%20three%20states.%20The%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samiti%20in%20Telangana%20is%20also%20reeling%20under%20corruption%20charges.%20These%20could%20help%20the%20Congress.%20However%2C%20a%20win%20by%20default%20is%20no%20long-term%20solution%20to%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20own%20weaknesses.%20If%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20is%20the%20person%20to%20lead%20the%20GOP%2C%20his%20vision%20needs%20sharper%20public%20projection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjay%20K.%20Mehra%20is%20former%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20Senior%20Fellow%2C%20Nehru%20Memorial%20Museum%20and%20Library%2C%202019-21.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700387098000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F19150848%2FF_Ioh-sXMAAaoYX.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-assembly-polls-are-a-litmus-test-for-congress-and-rahul-gandhi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22But%20a%20win%2C%20by%20default%2C%20is%20no%20long-term%20solution%20to%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20own%20weaknesses.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-assembly-polls-are-a-litmus-test-for-congress-and-rahul-gandhi%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Madhya%20Pradesh%3A%20Rural%20Workers%20Get%20Lowest%20Daily%20Wages%2C%20Below%20National%20Average%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F15142032%2F7655150258_30d4e48fdc_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0In%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20which%20went%20to%20the%20polls%20on%20Friday%20(November%2017)%2C%20rural%20agricultural%20workers%20get%20the%20lowest%20daily%20wages%20in%20the%20country%20below%20the%20national%20average%2C%20according%20to%20data%20compiled%20by%20RBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20national%20average%20for%20the%20year%20ended%20March%202023%20was%20Rs%20345.7%2C%20male%20agricultural%20workers%20in%20rural%20areas%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20got%20a%20daily%20wage%20of%20just%20Rs%20229.2%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Frural-workers-in-mp-gujarat-get-the-lowest-daily-wages-rbi-data-9032716%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520data%2520compiled%2520by%2Cthe%2520year%2520was%2520Rs%2520345.7%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20state%20that%20recorded%20the%20lowest%20daily%20wages%20was%20Gujarat%20where%20male%20agricultural%20workers%20got%20a%20daily%20wage%20of%20Rs%20241.9.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20poorly%20paid%20states%20include%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20where%20rural%20farm%20workers%20got%20an%20average%20daily%20wage%20of%20Rs%20309.3%20and%20Odisha%20Rs%20285.1%20in%202021-22.%20While%20in%20Maharashtra%20which%20is%20touted%20as%20an%20industrialised%20state%2C%20male%20farm%20workers%20got%20Rs%20303.5%20daily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20central%20bank%E2%80%99s%20data%2C%20a%20rural%20farm%20worker%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20will%20get%20a%20monthly%20earning%20of%20around%20Rs%205%2C730%20per%20month%20if%20he%20works%20for%2025%20days.%20In%20Gujarat%2C%20the%20monthly%20wage%20for%20a%20farm%20worker%20would%20have%20been%20around%20Rs%206%2C047.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%20a%20rural%20farm%20worker%20in%20Kerala%2C%20which%20pays%20the%20highest%20wage%20of%20Rs%20764.3%20per%20person%20among%20states%2C%20gets%20an%20average%20of%20Rs%2019%2C107%20for%2025%20days%20of%20work%20in%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fvideo-santosh-mehrotra-unemployment-unpaid-worker%5C%22%3EWhat%20India%E2%80%99s%20Growing%20Army%20of%20Unpaid%20Workers%20Means%20for%20It%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20said%20in%20the%20case%20of%20male%20non-agricultural%20workers%2C%20the%20lowest%20wage%20was%20again%20seen%20in%20MP%20with%20an%20average%20wage%20of%20Rs%20246.3%20while%20in%20Gujarat%20workers%20got%20a%20daily%20wage%20of%20Rs%20273.1%20and%20Tripura%20Rs%20280.6.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20average%20however%20was%20Rs%20348.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20non-agricultural%20workers%E2%80%99%20daily%20wages%2C%20Kerala%20leads%20states%20with%20Rs%20696.6%20per%20person.%20This%20is%20followed%20by%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20(Rs%20517.9)%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20(Rs%20481.5)%20and%20Haryana%20(Rs%20451)%20for%20the%20year%20ended%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20case%20of%20rural%20male%20construction%20workers%2C%20Gujarat%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20are%20once%20again%20at%20the%20bottom%20and%20below%20the%20national%20average%20of%20Rs%20393.3.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20Gujarat%20rural%20construction%20workers%20got%20an%20average%20wage%20of%20Rs%20323.2%2C%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20it%20was%20Rs%20278.7%20and%20Tripura%20Rs%20286.1%20per%20day%20during%20the%20fiscal%20ended%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20the%20daily%20wage%20for%20rural%20construction%20workers%20was%20Rs%20852.5%20in%20Kerala%2C%20Rs%20534.5%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Rs%20500.9%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Rs%20498.3%20in%20Himachal%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20data%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Feconomy%2Frural-workers-in-mp-gujarat-get-the-lowest-daily-wages-rbi-data-9032716%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520data%2520compiled%2520by%2Cthe%2520year%2520was%2520Rs%2520345.7%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RBI%20report%20said%20that%20extreme%20weather%20events%20remain%20a%20key%20factor%20as%20rural%20jobs%20are%20dependent%20on%20agriculture%20which%20is%20dependent%20on%20monsoon%20and%20%3Cem%3Erabi%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekharif%3C%2Fem%3E%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIncreasing%20frequency%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20therefore%2C%20remain%20a%20key%20monitor-able.%20While%20lowering%20of%20demand%20for%20MGNREGA%20jobs%20is%20an%20encouraging%20sign%20for%20the%20rural%20economy%20from%20a%20job%20perspective%2C%20depressed%20wages%20are%20a%20matter%20of%20concern%20for%20rural%20demand%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20RBI%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20an%20increase%20had%20been%20recorded%20in%20the%20pace%20of%20wage%20growth%20for%20agricultural%20and%20non-agricultural%20labourers.%20It%20reached%20an%20intra-year%20peak%20of%207.7%25%20in%20January%202023%20and%205.6%25%20in%20November%202022%2C%20respectively%2C%20before%20moderating%20in%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700386805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F03%2F15142032%2F7655150258_30d4e48fdc_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fmadhya-pradesh-rural-workers-get-lowest-daily-wages-below-national-average%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22RBI%20data%20showed%20that%20while%20the%20national%20average%20for%20the%20year%2