rted%20planting%201%2C000%20trees%20on%20the%20roadside%20of%20Ulli%20village%20in%20Gudiyatham.%20He%20also%20took%20responsibility%20for%20maintaining%20the%20trees%2C%20and%20in%20six%20short%20months%2C%20they%20grew%20well.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20used%20to%20be%20a%20social%20forest%20on%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Palar%20river%2C%20that%20I%20would%20cross%20on%20my%20way%20to%20school%20every%20day.%20It%20was%20slowly%20taken%20over%20by%20the%20land%20mafia%20and%20all%20the%20trees%20were%20cut.%20It%20became%20a%20barren%20wasteland%20which%20was%20just%20used%20for%20sand.%20I%20wanted%20to%20restore%20and%20recreate%20that%20forest%2C%20which%20was%20home%20to%20so%20many%20birds%2C%20insects%20and%20monkeys.%20I%20would%20keep%20giving%20petitions%20to%20the%20district%20collector%20every%20week%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail%2C%E2%80%9D%20Srikanth%20tells%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20concept%20of%20social%20forestry%20is%20to%20involve%20locals%20of%20the%20region%20in%20the%20afforestation%20of%20unused%20wastelands%2C%20and%20to%20also%20protect%20and%20preserve%20them%20from%20rapid%20deforestation.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20social%20forest%2C%20people%20can%20come%20and%20go%20unlike%20a%20reserved%20forest%2C%20where%20no%20one%20is%20allowed%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Srikanth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20saw%20many%20monkeys%20getting%20hurt%20on%20the%20roads%2C%20which%20bothered%20him%20greatly.%20%E2%80%9CMany%20birds%20and%20monkeys%20would%20be%20wounded.%20They%20had%20no%20place%20to%20go%20to%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%201%2C000%20trees%20that%20he%20planted%20grew%20well%2C%20his%20efforts%20were%20noticed%20by%20the%20local%20authorities%20and%20reached%20the%20attention%20of%20then%20collector%2C%20A%20Shanmuga%20Sundaram.%20Srikanth%20recalls%20that%20Sundaram%20offered%20him%20help.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20asked%20Sundaram%20to%20help%2